-- Apple Rises in Late Trading After Verdict in Samsung Patent Case
-- B y   T o m   G i l e s
-- 2012-08-25T02:18:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-24/apple-rises-in-late-trading-after-verdict-in-samsung-patent-case.html
Apple Inc. (AAPL)  rose in late trading after the company scored a victory in a patent dispute against Samsung Electronics Co.  A California jury found that Samsung infringed six of seven patents for mobile devices and awarded Apple more than $1.05 billion in damages.  Shares climbed to as high as $675.94 in late trading as the verdicts were delivered in federal court in  San Jose , California. The stock had climbed less than 1 percent to $663.22 at the close today in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story: Tom Giles in  San Francisco  at   tgiles5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story: Tom Giles at   tgiles5@bloomberg.net  